docs.abstract: Faced with an unrelenting protest over proposed changes in France’s generous pension system, officials withdraw a move to raise the full-benefit retirement age to 64 from the present 62.
docs.snippet: Faced with an unrelenting protest over proposed changes in France’s generous pension system, officials withdraw a move to raise the full-benefit retirement age to 64 from the present 62.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — With tens of thousands of anti-government demonstrators once again coursing through the streets of Paris and other cities and clouds of tear gas and smashed store windows punctuating the urban landscape, the French government made a major concession on Saturday to unions protesting its pension reform plan.

headline.main: Macron Scraps Proposal to Raise Retirement Age in France
headline.print_headline: Macron Pulls Back in Pension Brawl With Strikers

docs.abstract: The 49ers defeated the Vikings, 27-10, in dominating fashion, including two rushing touchdowns and by capitalizing on Vikings mistakes.
docs.snippet: The 49ers defeated the Vikings, 27-10, in dominating fashion, including two rushing touchdowns and by capitalizing on Vikings mistakes.
docs.lead_paragraph: SANTA CLARA, Calif. — The greats came back on Saturday, flooding a frothing Levi’s Stadium to watch their treasured San Francisco 49ers engage in a pastime foreign to their fan base for so long: playoff football. Joe Montana, Jerry Rice, Bryant Young — they all showed up, flocking to witness the latest stage of the 49ers’ revival, six years in the making.

headline.main: How the 49ers Beat the Vikings to Advance to the N.F.C. Championship Game

docs.abstract: The Ravens came into the playoffs as the top seed in the A.F.C., but quarterback Ryan Tannehill turned the game into a rout for Tennessee by outplaying Lamar Jackson.
docs.snippet: The Ravens came into the playoffs as the top seed in the A.F.C., but quarterback Ryan Tannehill turned the game into a rout for Tennessee by outplaying Lamar Jackson.
docs.lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE — Baltimore Ravens quarterback Lamar Jackson was the N.F.L.’s most dominating player this season, which is why he is the prohibitive favorite to win the league’s Most Valuable Player Award. But as the postseason approached, Jackson’s attention quickly turned to trying to deliver similarly stellar results in the playoffs, especially since he had played poorly in his playoff debut last season in an upset home loss to the Los Angeles Chargers.

headline.main: How the Titans Beat the Ravens to Advance to the A.F.C. Championship Game
headline.print_headline: Jackson and the Top-Seeded Ravens Fall Apart

byline.original: By Bill Pennington and Kevin Draper

docs.abstract: The crisis of English departments is also a crisis of faith.
docs.snippet: The crisis of English departments is also a crisis of faith.
docs.lead_paragraph: This column tries to keep its cool, but last week I briefly surrendered to crisis and existential dread, to the sense that an entire world is dissolving underneath our feet — institutions crumbling, authorities corrupted, faith in the whole experiment evaporating.

docs.abstract: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.snippet: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2006, Google bought YouTube for more than $1 billion, Apple was preparing to announce the first iPhone, and the American housing bubble began to deflate. Claire Stapleton, then a senior at the University of Pennsylvania, faced the same question over and over: What did she plan to do with that English degree? She flirted, noncommittally, with Teach for America.

docs.abstract: The victory was a remarkable comeback for Ms. Tsai and suggested that Beijing’s pressure campaign had backfired.
docs.snippet: The victory was a remarkable comeback for Ms. Tsai and suggested that Beijing’s pressure campaign had backfired.
docs.lead_paragraph: TAIPEI, Taiwan — Taiwan’s voters delivered a stinging rebuke of China’s rising authoritarianism on Saturday by re-electing President Tsai Ing-wen, who vowed to preserve the island’s sovereignty in the face of Beijing’s intensifying efforts to bring it under its control.

headline.main: In Blow to Beijing, Taiwan Re-elects Tsai Ing-wen as President
headline.print_headline: Taiwan Voters Re-elect President in a Rebuke To Beijing’s Authority

docs.abstract: Not that long ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were golden in the eyes of the news media and public. What happened?
docs.snippet: Not that long ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were golden in the eyes of the news media and public. What happened?
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Once upon a short time ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were lauded as the breath of fresh air that the British monarchy needed to become more inclusive and modern.

headline.main: Harry, Meghan and Britain: When Did the Fairy Tale Go Sour?
headline.print_headline: The Duke, the Duchess and Britain: When Did the Fairy Tale Go Sour?

docs.abstract: Andrew J. Ries gives us a stairway to, well, both places.
docs.snippet: Andrew J. Ries gives us a stairway to, well, both places.
docs.lead_paragraph: SATURDAY PUZZLE — Andrew J. Ries, our constructor today, has hit for the crossword cycle, and then some: He’s done grids for every day of the week and even a few Sunday variety puzzles. Most of his grids come on the weekends,  so weekend solvers  get to sample his wares pretty often and gain some familiarity.

docs.abstract: Wolf Cukier, 17, was analyzing brightness of stars during an internship with NASA last year when he made the discovery.
docs.snippet: Wolf Cukier, 17, was analyzing brightness of stars during an internship with NASA last year when he made the discovery.
docs.lead_paragraph: The summer before senior year of high school can be a stressful time for a teenager. Childhood is winding down. College applications loom large. Many students are looking for an edge that will help them get into the right school. Last year, Wolf Cukier, 17, spent his summer vacation as few other rising seniors have: He helped discover a planet.

headline.main: How’s Your Internship Going? This Teen Found a Planet
headline.print_headline: College Application Bonus: I Helped Discover a Planet

docs.abstract: Officials warned of floods, hail and snow as the vast storm moved east.
docs.snippet: Officials warned of floods, hail and snow as the vast storm moved east.
docs.lead_paragraph: A fast-moving storm packing a litany of hazards — tornadoes, floods, severe storms and more — raged through the southern United States on Saturday, leaving at least 10 people dead and a trail of destruction in its wake.

headline.main: 10 Die in Storm as Tornadoes and Squalls Pummel U.S.
headline.print_headline: Storms Pummel the Midwest and the South, Killing at Least 9
